  "text": "higher antigen-specific response than circulatory memory cells isolated from lymphoid tissues [CITATION_1] . T RM can even respond more rapidly to tissue infection than circulatory memory cells [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The T RM cell population within each tissue is capable of recognizing the specific pathogens that most commonly affect those tissues, and T RM cells remain in place long after pathogen elimination [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
